<p><strong>Let's meet at Humanities at 12:20p.  Bring your bike and a lock, for I'm leaning toward some type of duathlon.</strong></p>
<p>I wore my running shoes today.  I view this less as a lack of faith in our ability to ride into the teeth of 40mph winds and more as the expression of a desire to wear bright orange shoes.  You, O'Gentle Readers, will understand, I'm sure.</p>
<p>In any event, today more than ever, the Frenzy needs your help.  If you have a window in your office, please post your weather observations as comments before the noon hour.  Your readings will help decide our fate today!  Bon courage!</p>